":"1363–Deceased","1469":"1469","1413":"1413","1400":"1400","1452":"1452","1396":"1396","1363":"1363","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","London, , Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","London, England":"London, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Machyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Czech Alois, Zdenka.","Czech (<b>Macháň</b>) and Slovak (also <b>Machán</b>): from a derivative of the personal name   Mach  .","English (Yorkshire): variant of   Machen  . It is also found in Lanarkshire, Scotland."],"variants":[{"name":"Mach","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Huy, Minh, To, Hoa, Hung, Muoi, Quang, Tan, Anh, Binh, Chau, Chuc.","Czech, Slovak, Polish, Ukrainian, and Sorbian: from the personal name <i>Mach</i>, a pet form of names beginning with <i>Ma-</i>, e.g. <i>Matěj</i> in Czech (see   Matej  ),   Martin   in Slovak, and   Maciej   in Polish.","Possibly also an Americanized form of Hungarian <b>Mács</b>: from a pet form of <i>Máté</i> or <i>Mátyás</i>, Hungarian forms of the personal name   Matthew  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Machyn was born as the son of Sir William Machyn and Mrs. Mary Machyn. He married Julia Whelsey in 1400, in London, Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1452, in Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–1452":"–1452","–1413":"–1413","1390–1469":"1390–1469","1360–1396":"1360–1396","1363–Female":"1363–Surnud","1469":"1469","1413":"1413","1400":"1400","1452":"1452","1396":"1396","1363":"1363","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","London, , Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England":"London, England"},"fi":{"–1452":"–1452","–1413":"–1413","1390–1469":"1390–1469","1360–1396":"1360–1396","1363–Female":"1363–Kuollut","1469":"1469","1413":"1413","1400":"1400","1452":"1452","1396":"1396","1363":"1363","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","London, , Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","London, England":"London, England"},"fr":{"–1452":"–1452","–1413":"–1413","1390–1469":"1390–1469","1360–1396":"1360–1396","1363–Female":"1363–Décédée","1469":"1469","1413":"1413","1400":"1400","1452":"1452","1396":"1396","1363":"1363","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","London, , Middlesex, England":"Londres, Middlesex, Angleterre","Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","London, England":"Londres, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Machyn est né, fils de Sir William Machyn et Mrs. Mary Machyn. Il a épousé Julia Whelsey en 1400, à Londres, Middlesex, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1452, à Wilbarston, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"–1452":"–1452","–1413":"–1413","1390–1469":"1390–1469","1360–1396":"1360–1396